This paper discusses a novel approach to solving sequential prediction problems using a combination of learning to search and recurrent neural networks. The paper focuses on the application of this approach to imitation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning that involves learning from demonstrations. Given the focus on machine learning and neural networks, as well as the specific application to imitation learning, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.RO (Robotics).
